    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "a9161820_ab4d536d",
        "filename": "grpc/prpc/client.go",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 127,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-01-25T22:19:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "this is a good insight in general, but can you think of other reasons?\nI feel like we\u0027d forever-complicate the API for the sake of something temporary. It is not hard to update servers to use the latest version of pRPC lib; unless the server is in Python. \n\nprpc clients are often created as myprotopackage.NewFoobarClient(\u0026prpc.Client{...}), i.e. without reusing the prpc client.\n\nThe alternative to a callback, is a recommendation here that they should create two separate clients if one server supports compression and another doesn\u0027t, and bet that it will never happen in practice.\n\nWDYT?",
      "parentUuid": "33b6d526_97902e23",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 127,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 127,
        "endChar": 25
      },
